***


***"flexbox, grid, positioning, transforms, & multi-column", all can alter the visual order for any content.***

***All elements must provide all the different features of the element being cloned.***

*** We can then use JavaScript to program all the functionality of the element it is moching.***

***disabled is not "Global". <disabled> applies to
 {
<button>, <input>, <optgroup>, <option>, <select>, <textarea>,  <fieldset>.  <optgroup> <fieldset>, <legend>.
}
***

***The same elements that also support disabled are also (targetable) with  :disabled and :enabled classes.***

***To renable a disabled element, most of the time it has to be removed with:
Element.removeAttribute('disabled')
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
**In this example we use TabIndex:

<p>Click in any input, then press the tab key.</p>
<ol>
  <li><input tabindex="3" ></li>
  <li><input tabindex="6" ></li>
  <li><input tabindex="2" ></li>
  <li><input tabindex="0" ></li>
  <li><input tabindex="0"></li>
  <li><input tabindex="-1"></li>
  <li><input tabindex="0"></li>
  <li><input tabindex="8"></li>
  <li><input tabindex="1"></li>
  <li><input tabindex="5"></li>
  <li><input tabindex="7"></li>
  <li><input tabindex="4"></li>
</ol>


**CSS Value:
:root { font-family: segoe UI, system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif}

input, ol {font-size: 2rem}
input { width: 5rem;}
input:focus {
  background-color: palegoldenrod;
  border-color: green;
  outline: 2px solid red;
}
ol {columns: 4 7rem;}

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
*** In this example we use the CSS to customize a bit more***

<p><label>Place your cursor in the text box, then press your tab key several times:<input/></label></p>
<div>
  <span tabindex="0">flexbox.</span>
  <span tabindex="0">CSS </span>
  <span tabindex="0">with</span>
  <span tabindex="0">styled </span>
  <span tabindex="0">then</span>
  <span tabindex="0">This</span>
  <span tabindex="0">order</span>
  <span tabindex="0">reverse</span>
  <span tabindex="0">in</span>
  <span tabindex="0">written</span>
  <span tabindex="0">was </span>
  <span tabindex="0">sentenced</span>
</div>

**CSS Value:

:root { font-family: segoe UI, system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif}
div {
  display: inline-flex;
  flex-flow: row-reverse; 
  gap: 0.5em; 
}
span:nth-of-type(6) {
  order: 3;
}
span { border: 1px dashed;}
span:focus {
  background-color: palegoldenrod;
  border-color: green;
  outline: 2px solid red;
}

***In this <flex-flow: row-reverse;>  reverses the visual order.***
